- **Neuron #14** — dedicated detector for 'H'. Zero cross-activation with similar characters.
- **Neuron #12** — activates solely on ',' (comma). Separate circuit for punctuation vs. letters.

This is the "Grandmother Cell" hypothesis — one neuron, one concept.`
